    "en": {
      "title": "Missile attack on Ukrainian malls",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A missile strike on a shopping mall in central Ukraine's Kremenchuk has killed at least 16 people and wounded 59 others, the head of Ukraine's emergency services says.",
        "\"At present we know that 16 people have died and 59 have been injured. 25 of them have been hospitalized. The information is being updated,\" said Sergei Kruk.",
        "Ukrainian President Selensky said in a telegram on Monday that more than 1,000 civilians were inside the mall when the missile struck, and blamed Russia for the attack.",
        "The mall is roughly the size of two football fields and the attack took place around 4pm. Photographs from the scene show heavy smoke billowing from the building, which was engulfed in flames."
      ],
